videoSnippet.title: Nakamura Defeats Karjakin in Chess.com Speed Chess Championship
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Read entire article here  https://www.chess.com/news/view/nakamura-beats-karjakin-to-play-carlsen-in-speed-chess-final

Hikaru Nakamura qualified for the Chess.com Speed Chess Championship Final on 3 January 2018 where he will meet Magnus Carlsen. On Saturday Nakamura defeated Sergey Karjakin in a tight match with lots of draws.

It's not for nothing that Carlsen and Nakamura are known to be the two best speed chess players on the planet. For the second year in a row, the two stars qualified for Chess.com's finalâ€”in the 2016 GM Blitz Battle, and now in the 2017 Speed Chess Championship.

Hikaru Nakamura VS Sergey Karjakin
Speedchess Championship Semi-finals
16.12.2017 on Chess.com

1. b3 e5 2. Bb2 Nc6 3. e3 Nf6 4. Bb5 Bd6 5. Na3 e4 6. Nc4 Be7 7. Bxc6 bxc6 8. f3 O-O 9. fxe4 Nxe4 10. Nf3 Bf6 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. O-O Ba6 13. d3 Bxc4 14. bxc4 d5 15. cxd5 cxd5 16. Nd4 Qe7 17. Nf5 Qe5 18. Qf3 g6 19. Nd4 Kg7 20. Rab1 c5 21. Nb3 Rfe8 22. Kh1 c4 23. dxc4 dxc4 24. Nd4 Rac8 25. Rb7 a5 26. Rb6 Ne4 27. Qxf7+ Kh8 28. Rb7 Ng5 29. Qf2 Re7 30. Nc6 Nh3 31. Qf3
